example 

to sort human reable data use -h option not -n
===========

archieve
create and restore

tar -cvf ourarchieve.tar file[1-3].txt
file1.txt
file2.txt
file3.txt
]$ ls
file1.txt  file2.txt  file3.txt  ourarchieve.tar

find tar folder
ls -l | grep .tar 
-rw-r--r--. 1 ec2-user ec2-user 10240 Aug 20 11:11 ourarchieve.tar


compress

gzip ourarchieve.tar 
[ec2-user@ip-172-31-25-240 ~]$ ls
beautiful.txt  file1.txt  file2.txt  file3.txt  file4.txt  number.txt  ourarchieve.tar.gz
